abstract: The telecommunications company, which lost exclusive rights to the iPhone, reported a 39 percent increase in first-quarter profit.
snippet: The telecommunications company, which lost exclusive rights to the iPhone, reported a 39 percent increase in first-quarter profit.
lead_paragraph: AT&T, the nation’s largest telecommunications company, reported a 39 percent increase in its first-quarter profit on Wednesday, despite losing the exclusive rights to sell the iPhone in the United States midway through the period.
